    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** - May 21, 2026\n\n---\n\n## ☢️ Moscow added nukes to the notification stack\n\nRussia and Belarus ran the final stage of nuclear drills, because subtlety remains unavailable in the Kremlin settings menu.\n\n- **The exercise:** AP says trucks with intercontinental ballistic missiles, nuclear submarines and warplanes joined three-day maneuvers ending Thursday.\n- **The Belarus layer:** Lukashenko inspected Russian nuclear-capable Iskander missiles, while Belarus also hosts Russia's Oreshnik intermediate-range system.\n- **The signal:** the drills followed Ukrainian drone strikes near Moscow and repeated drone incidents over NATO territory, including a Vilnius shelter warning and airport closure.\n\n*The message discipline is crude, but nobody can claim the font size is small.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/russia-nuclear-drill-belarus-ukraine-cce4ba1be04956f7a91222a24c61a819)\n\n---\n\n## 🛢️ Ukraine kept drilling Russia's oil wallet\n\nKyiv's long-range campaign has found the dullest possible strategic target: refinery throughput, which is exactly why it matters.\n\n- **The strike:** AP says Zelenskyy reported Ukrainian drones hitting the Syzran refinery, more than 800 kilometers inside Russia, with video showing heavy smoke.\n- **The toll:** Samara's governor said two people were killed by drones in Syzran, while Russia's Astra said the Rosneft-owned refinery was struck.\n- **The pattern:** Zelenskyy said May's long-range plan is focused on refineries, storage facilities and other infrastructure tied to Russian oil revenues.\n\n*The war economy now gets its pressure applied by combustion accounting.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/russia-ukraine-war-drones-oil-refinery-f7864b14631e19e608b0904d606473b5)\n\n---\n\n## 🏛️ Congress found the Iran clock again\n\nAfter two months of war, lawmakers are once more consulting the constitutional feature they keep discovering under pressure.\n\n- **The vote:** AP says the House was expected Thursday to vote on forcing Trump to withdraw from the Iran war under the 1973 War Powers Resolution.\n- **The math:** a similar House measure tied last week after three Republicans backed it; the Senate advanced its version Tuesday with four GOP votes.\n- **The pressure:** Hormuz disruption has lifted U.S. gasoline prices, with Democrats citing a $4.53 national average outside the Capitol.\n\n*War powers remain America's most recurring reminder notification.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/iran-war-donald-trump-congress-vote-8038c7f9552186716d01f910d6a0d356)\n\n---\n\n## 🇪🇺 Europe offered Ukraine the waiting-room badge\n\nGermany wants a faster political lane for Kyiv, which is what happens when accession talks meet war, Hungary and calendar fatigue.\n\n- **The proposal:** AP saw a letter from Chancellor Friedrich Merz urging the EU to consider Ukraine associate membership while reviving talks with Russia.\n- **The access:** Ukraine would join EU meetings without voting rights and gain non-voting associate roles in the Commission and Parliament.\n- **The condition:** Merz says the plan would go beyond the existing association agreement and include a snap-back mechanism if democratic standards slip.\n\n*Not membership light, Berlin insists. Very well: membership adjacent, with paperwork.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/europe-ukraine-membership-russia-merz-negotiations-f1c0b453fe6339858ad6c7932ce4e432)"
  }
]
